---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Divider from '../components/Divider.astro';
import SocialMedia from '../components/SocialMedia.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { SECTIONS, TECH_STACK, SOCIAL_MEDIA } from '../consts'; 

import leetcodeImage from '../assets/about/leetcode.webp';
import studysession from '../assets/about/studysession.webp';
import gardenharvest from '../assets/about/radish.webp';
import rocqcode from '../assets/about/rocq.webp';

const currentLanguages = Object.values(TECH_STACK.CURRENT).filter(lang => lang !== "Rust");
const futureLanguages = Object.values(TECH_STACK.FUTURE);
---

<MainLayout title="But, Who Am I?" subtitle="what do I do in my day-to-day? why is there a crab at the top?">
  <section class="about-content">
      <div class="social-media">
        <p>These are my "social media":</p>
        <SocialMedia />
      </div>

      <Divider />

      <section class="bio">
        <p>
          Well, my (real) name is <strong data-bio="real-name">Carlos</strong>, but you can call 
          me <strong data-bio="nickname">Aru</strong> (ngl, I really like it!).
        </p>

        <p>
          I'm a 22-year-old <strong data-bio="cs">Computer Science</strong> student, and that's the 
          reason why I'm really into everything about low-level programming; I fell in love with 
          how things work under thehood.
        </p>

        <p>
          My favorite language is <strong data-lang="Rust">Rust</strong>, and as you can imagine, 
          that's the reason for that cute, tiny, eye-catching crab moving side to side at the top 
          of the page. Although, I usually program in:
        </p>

        <div class="lang-row">
          {currentLanguages.map((lang) => (
          <strong class="lang-text" data-lang={lang}>{lang}</strong>
          ))}
        </div>

        <p>Also, I'd like to learn:</p>

        <div class="lang-row">
          {futureLanguages.map((lang) => (
          <strong class="lang-text" data-lang={lang}>{lang}</strong>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section>
        <p>
          This year (2026), I discovered two CS fields that made me love this area even more: 
          <a 
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analysis_of_algorithms"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >Analysis of Algorithms</a>,
          and <a 
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formal_verification"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >Formal Verification</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          During the 2026-1 semester (2025), I took <strong data-exp="AA">Analysis of Algorithms</strong>
          and fell in love immediately after hearing about some research experiences from the course's 
          instructor. He talked about weird theorems to prove some kind of relationship between 
          data, concluding, "Hmm... one cannot do it faster than O(log n) ☝️🤓," or the 
          relationship between 
          <a 
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matroid"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >Matroids</a> and 
          <a 
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greedy_algorithm"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >Greedy algorithms</a>.
          The 2026-2 semester (this year) blew my mind beyond my expectations. I took 
          <strong data-exp="AAII">Analysis of Algorithms II</strong>, and that was awesome! 
          Actually, you can read about my experience
          <a 
            href="https://aruzdh.dev/blog/four-months-studying-computational-geometry/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >here!</a>
        </p>

        <p>
          Yet, the field that made me say "can't wait to go home and carry out that proof!" was 
          <strong data-exp="FV">Formal Verification</strong>. At the same time, I was taking a 
          course about
          <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_logic"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >Mathematical Logic</a>,
          so they complemented each other perfectly. That said, my main interest is in 
          <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rocq">Rocq</a>—I'll write about it soon!
        </p>

        <figure class="display-box rocq-box">
          <Image src={rocqcode} alt="Rocq Code" /> 
          <figcaption>My Rocq workspace.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p>
          <strong data-log="date">In November 2024</strong> I decided to create an X/Twitter 
          account with the main purpose of sharing my CS life. I quickly found a friendly community 
          called <strong data-log="study-bud">"Study Buddy"</strong> where lots of people share 
          their personal <strong data-log="notes">notes</strong>, 
          <strong data-log="POV">study-session POV</strong>, 
          <strong data-log="setups">setups</strong>, and several other 
          <strong data-log="aesthetic-things">aesthetic things</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
          For instance, this is my usual view when 
          <strong data-log="home">I'm studying at home</strong>. It looks nice, doesn't it?
        </p>

        <figure class="display-box">
          <Image src={studysession} alt="CS study session" />
          <figcaption>Home study environment.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p class="logical-problems">
          One of the things I enjoy the most is solving logic problems. I'm sure you're familiar 
          with platforms like{" "} <strong data-site="LeetCode">LeetCode</strong> (my favorite btw 
        ☝🏽🤓),{" "} <strong data-site="HackerRank">HackerRank</strong>, 
          <strong data-site="CodeForces">CodeForces</strong>, and so on. I spend around 2 hours a 
          day solving these kinds of problems.
        </p>

        <p>If you want to check out my profile, here's my LeetCode:</p>

        <figure class="display-box leetcode-box">
          <Image src={leetcodeImage} alt="LeetCode profile" /> 
          <div class="action-footer">
            <a href={SOCIAL_MEDIA.LEETCODE} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="profile-btn">
              {"=> "} VIEW_LEETCODE_PROFILE
            </a>
          </div>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p>
          Yup, I've talked about my current studies, my favorite languages, and my obsession with 
          LeetCode, but what do I do when I'm not programming? Do I play LoL like an average CS or 
          SWE?
        </p>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <section class="activity-log">
        <p>
          I love <strong data-log="gardening">gardening</strong>. For a few months now, I've been growing various 
          veggies in my garden. My dad grew up in a rural area, so he knows a lot about this 
          wonderful world.
        </p>

        <p>
          Actually ☝🏽🤓, that's the reason I developed a garden organizer, which you can (actually, 
          it's gone, but you can take a look at my other projects lol) view in the{" "}
          <a href="/projects">{SECTIONS.PROJECTS}</a> tab.
        </p>

        <p class="gardening-text">
          At the moment, I'm growing coriander, tomato, round zucchini, corn, carrot, and a couple 
          more veggies. In the <a href="/life">{SECTIONS.LIFE}</a> tab, you'll find some photos 
          I've taken so far.
        </p>

        <figure class="display-box garden-box">
          <Image src={gardenharvest} alt="Garden harvest" />
          <figcaption>First radish harvest.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  strong[data-lang="Rust"], strong[data-lang="OCaml"], strong[data-log="home"], 
  strong[data-exp="AA"] {
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  strong[data-lang="C++"], strong[data-lang="Python"], strong[data-lang="C"],
  strong[data-bio="real-name"], strong[data-site="CodeForces"] {
    color: var(--blue);
  }

  strong[data-lang="Haskell"] {
    color: var(--purple0)
  }

  strong[data-log="date"], strong[data-log="aesthetic-things"] {
    color: var(--purple1)
  }

  strong[data-lang="Java"], strong[data-log=setups], strong[data-exp="FV"] {
    color: var(--red)
  }

  strong[data-lang="TypeScript"], strong[data-lang="Go"], strong[data-log="study-bud"] {
    color: var(--cyan)
  }

  strong[data-lang="Zig"], strong[data-bio="cs"], strong[data-log="notes"], 
  strong[data-site="LeetCode"] {
    color: var(--yellow)
  }

  strong[data-bio="nickname"], strong[data-log="POV"], strong[data-site="HackerRank"],
  strong[data-log="gardening"], strong[data-exp="AAII"] {
    color: var(--green);
  }

  .lang-row {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .lang-text {
    color: var(--fg-light);
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .lang-text::before {
    content: "· ";
    color: var(--blue);
    margin-right: 0.25rem;
  }

  .display-box {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .display-box img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    margin: 0 auto 0.75rem;
  }

  .garden-box img {
    max-width: 400px;
  }

  .leetcode-box img {
    max-width: 550px;
  }

  figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--fg-light);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .action-footer {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .profile-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--blue);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
  }

  .profile-btn:hover {
    background-color: var(--blue);
    color: var(--bg);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--blue);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .gardening-text {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
</style>
